    14063 Introduction to electrical circuit analysis for electrical and computer engineering. Analysis and design of DC and AC circuits including resistors, capacitors, inductors, and transformers. Applications of Ohm’s Law, Kirchhoff’s Laws, network theorems, transient and frequency domain analysis will be investigated. Hands-on laboratory exercises are also included. course-description\main.js 2018-06-25T11:13:44-06:00
